Aquaduino is a free open source controlling framework based on the Arduino Mega 2560.
It is mainly developed for controlling fresh-water and salt-water aquaria.

Main features:
	* Management of multiple actuators, controllers and sensors.
		* Actuators can freely be assigned to the available controllers.
		* Available sensing tasks and controller tasks are called in FIFO order and run to completion.
	* Network support
		* DHCP & Static IP configuration
		* NTP synchronization
	* Extensible webinterface.
		* Network configuration
		* Controller configuration
		* Actuator configuration
	* Extensible configuration management interface.
		* Support for SD card storage